1
00:00:01,001 --> 00:00:02,585
<i><b>We ask you all to come here today</b></i>

2
00:00:02,669 --> 00:00:05,171
<i><b>to give a statement about</b></i>
<i><b>the death of Anton Montenegro</b></i>

3
00:00:05,255 --> 00:00:07,632
<i><b>and an incident</b></i>
<i><b>that happened 14 years ago.</b></i>

4
00:00:09,134 --> 00:00:12,887
<i><b>Autopsy reports prove</b></i>
<i><b>that Anton was two hours dead</b></i>

5
00:00:12,971 --> 00:00:14,723
<i><b>when they found</b></i>
<i><b>his body inside Ryan's shop.</b></i>

6
00:00:14,806 --> 00:00:16,850
<i><b>We are certain</b></i>
<i><b>that we know who killed Anton.</b></i>

7
00:00:16,933 --> 00:00:19,477
<i><b>It's the escaped convict Edong Santiago,</b></i>

8
00:00:19,561 --> 00:00:22,522
<i><b>who went to prison</b></i>
<i><b>for the murder of our friend Louisa Soria.</b></i>

9
00:00:22,605 --> 00:00:25,650
<i><b>And the reason</b></i>
<i><b>he escaped is to get his revenge on us.</b></i>

10
00:00:25,734 --> 00:00:27,819
<i><b>I'm here to take my aunt's body.</b></i>

11
00:00:27,902 --> 00:00:29,529
<i><b>To give her a proper burial.</b></i>

12
00:00:29,612 --> 00:00:30,780
<i><b>He didn't kill them.</b></i>

13
00:00:30,864 --> 00:00:31,948
<i><b>He's already dragged</b></i>
<i><b>so many people into this.</b></i>

14
00:00:32,032 --> 00:00:34,617
<i><b>With every killing and act of revenge,</b></i>
<i><b>he just got worse.</b></i>

15
00:00:34,701 --> 00:00:38,038
<i><b>Lying comes with a price.</b></i>

16
00:00:38,121 --> 00:00:40,165
<i><b>Liars!</b></i>

17
00:00:40,248 --> 00:00:43,042
<i><b>For sixteen years,</b></i>
<i><b>you ran away from what you did to mother.</b></i>

18
00:00:43,126 --> 00:00:45,086
<i><b>Now, I'll make sure you rot in prison!</b></i>

19
00:00:45,170 --> 00:00:46,880
<i><b>You ruined our lives!</b></i>

20
00:00:47,797 --> 00:00:54,846
<b>[theme music playing]</b>

21
00:02:03,665 --> 00:02:05,291
<b>[Lucas] Hurry up!</b>

22
00:02:05,917 --> 00:02:07,335
<b>Move!</b>

23
00:02:08,920 --> 00:02:09,963
<b>Sir.</b>

24
00:02:10,964 --> 00:02:13,091
<b>This is my father, Crisanto Santiago.</b>

25
00:02:13,842 --> 00:02:15,510
<b>Sixteen years ago,</b>

26
00:02:16,302 --> 00:02:18,012
<b>this bastard killed my mother!</b>

27
00:02:18,096 --> 00:02:21,975
<b>[uneasy music playing]</b>

28
00:02:25,186 --> 00:02:27,689
<b>There's an existing warrant</b>
<b>for his arrest.</b>

29
00:02:27,772 --> 00:02:30,150
<b>Yes. For parricide.</b>

30
00:02:31,109 --> 00:02:32,777
<b>There's another one. Just from last year.</b>

31
00:02:32,861 --> 00:02:34,529
<b>Robbery-homicide in Cavite.</b>

32
00:02:36,406 --> 00:02:38,158
<b>We need to coordinate that with their RTC.</b>

33
00:02:38,241 --> 00:02:41,077
<b>-Yes, sir.</b>
<b>-[Crisanto coughs]</b>

34
00:02:43,538 --> 00:02:45,748
<b>You know how I lost this?</b>

35
00:02:48,251 --> 00:02:51,921
<b>Some bastard cop shot me while chasing me.</b>

36
00:02:53,464 --> 00:02:57,010
<b>He knew I couldn't go to a hospital.</b>

37
00:02:58,094 --> 00:03:00,638
<b>It got infected.</b>

38
00:03:01,264 --> 00:03:02,515
<b>So they had to cut it off!</b>

39
00:03:04,767 --> 00:03:06,311
<b>[Delos Santos] Hold him.</b>

40
00:03:07,854 --> 00:03:09,647
<b>Crisanto Santiago,</b>

41
00:03:09,731 --> 00:03:13,818
<b>you are under arrest</b>
<b>for robbery and homicide.</b>

42
00:03:13,902 --> 00:03:16,154
<b>You have the right to remain silent.</b>

43
00:03:16,237 --> 00:03:18,615
<b>-Anything you say--</b>
<b>-You're just like them!</b>

44
00:03:18,698 --> 00:03:20,074
<b>Bastard!</b>

45
00:03:21,534 --> 00:03:22,660
<b>[Delos Santos] Bring him to his cell!</b>

46
00:03:22,744 --> 00:03:28,249
<b>[uneasy music continues]</b>

47
00:03:28,333 --> 00:03:29,375
<b>Lucas!</b>

48
00:03:29,876 --> 00:03:30,919
<b>-Lucas!</b>
<b>-[sighs heavily]</b>

49
00:03:39,844 --> 00:03:41,971
<b>What mother wouldn't be angry?!</b>

50
00:03:42,555 --> 00:03:45,475
<b>They let the bastard who killed my son go!</b>

51
00:03:46,809 --> 00:03:50,605
<b>Didn't his wife admit she lied?!</b>

52
00:03:50,688 --> 00:03:52,273
<b>How could you believe them?</b>

53
00:03:52,982 --> 00:03:56,569
<b>Mel and all her friends are liars!</b>

54
00:03:56,653 --> 00:04:00,448
<i><b>I know they all had</b></i>
<i><b>something to do with my son's death!</b></i>

55
00:04:00,531 --> 00:04:03,034
<i><b>They were all in on it!</b></i>

56
00:04:03,117 --> 00:04:04,619
<i><b>I just know it!</b></i>

57
00:04:11,000 --> 00:04:13,127
<b>[Mel sobs]</b>

58
00:04:13,211 --> 00:04:15,129
<b>Are you sure about this?</b>

59
00:04:15,213 --> 00:04:21,344
<b>[uneasy music continues]</b>

60
00:04:22,053 --> 00:04:24,973
<b>[Mel gasps, sobs]</b>

61
00:04:28,685 --> 00:04:30,728
<b>[sniffles, sobs]</b>

62
00:04:34,857 --> 00:04:36,651
<b>[Mel] He looks so peaceful.</b>

63
00:04:39,195 --> 00:04:41,614
<b>All these years, Mom…</b>

64
00:04:43,950 --> 00:04:47,829
<b>All these years,</b>
<b>I was terrified because of him.</b>

65
00:04:47,912 --> 00:04:51,541
<b>[sobbing]</b>

66
00:04:51,624 --> 00:04:53,376
<b>I actually thought that…</b>

67
00:04:53,960 --> 00:04:56,337
<b>I'd be the one who'd end up like this.</b>

68
00:04:58,464 --> 00:05:00,675
<b>Am I a bad person, Mom?</b>

69
00:05:00,758 --> 00:05:03,094
<b>No, no, no.</b>

70
00:05:03,177 --> 00:05:05,888
<b>[sobs] Am I a bad person</b>
<b>for being relieved</b>

71
00:05:05,972 --> 00:05:09,017
<b>that he's the one in there and not me?</b>

72
00:05:09,100 --> 00:05:10,810
<b>I'm horrible, Ma.</b>

73
00:05:11,394 --> 00:05:13,521
<b>Am I a bad person?</b>

74
00:05:13,604 --> 00:05:17,900
<b>[sobbing]</b>

75
00:05:17,984 --> 00:05:22,363
<b>[somber music playing]</b>

76
00:05:22,447 --> 00:05:24,699
<b>I've told my truth, Mom.</b>

77
00:05:25,616 --> 00:05:30,580
<b>I've told my truth,</b>
<b>but why does it still feel so heavy?</b>

78
00:05:37,795 --> 00:05:38,755
<b>[sobs]</b>

79
00:05:39,464 --> 00:05:42,508
<b>Relief doesn't mean you're cruel, Mel.</b>

80
00:05:44,260 --> 00:05:46,345
<b>It means you survived.</b>

81
00:05:48,264 --> 00:05:52,894
<b>Yes, one truth won't</b>
<b>erase all the pain overnight.</b>

82
00:05:54,062 --> 00:05:55,396
<b>But, dear,</b>

83
00:05:55,480 --> 00:05:58,900
<b>you were able to see what was broken.</b>

84
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:02,403
<b>The abuse, the wound…</b>

85
00:06:03,780 --> 00:06:04,947
<b>the fear.</b>

86
00:06:05,490 --> 00:06:07,867
<b>You've done the hardest part.</b>

87
00:06:10,369 --> 00:06:14,332
<b>You faced it. You said it out loud.</b>

88
00:06:16,000 --> 00:06:19,045
<b>Now you start to heal.</b>

89
00:06:20,463 --> 00:06:22,965
<b>You're the one in control of your story.</b>

90
00:06:23,841 --> 00:06:27,512
<b>All the pain you carry in here…</b>

91
00:06:28,262 --> 00:06:30,139
<b>will become your strength.</b>

92
00:06:30,223 --> 00:06:37,021
<b>[somber music continues]</b>

93
00:06:37,939 --> 00:06:44,904
<b>[sobbing]</b>

94
00:06:50,743 --> 00:06:53,496
<b>[somber music fades]</b>

95
00:07:01,921 --> 00:07:08,594
<b>[gentle music playing]</b>

96
00:07:16,102 --> 00:07:18,438
<b>-Are you okay?</b>
<b>-Huh?</b>

97
00:07:24,068 --> 00:07:25,153
<b>[Lucas sniffles]</b>

98
00:07:26,654 --> 00:07:28,114
<b>I'm okay.</b>

99
00:07:28,197 --> 00:07:34,537
<b>[gentle music continues]</b>

100
00:07:35,496 --> 00:07:37,165
<b>For your wound.</b>

101
00:07:45,631 --> 00:07:46,549
<b>Give me your hand.</b>

102
00:07:52,054 --> 00:07:53,681
<b>[Lucas sniffles]</b>

103
00:07:56,267 --> 00:07:57,518
<b>Thanks.</b>

104
00:08:00,271 --> 00:08:03,858
<b>For so long, I've dreamed</b>
<b>of sending my father to prison.</b>

105
00:08:06,235 --> 00:08:08,488
<b>Of finally getting justice for Mama.</b>

106
00:08:11,532 --> 00:08:12,783
<b>Finally…</b>

107
00:08:13,493 --> 00:08:16,204
<b>[breathes deeply]</b>

108
00:08:17,497 --> 00:08:19,707
<b>…being able to breathe.</b>

109
00:08:20,291 --> 00:08:21,417
<b>Us.</b>

110
00:08:24,337 --> 00:08:26,422
<b>We can finally be happy.</b>

111
00:08:30,885 --> 00:08:33,262
<b>But why is it that even</b>
<b>though he's in jail now…</b>

112
00:08:35,598 --> 00:08:40,478
<b>[gentle music continues]</b>

113
00:08:40,561 --> 00:08:41,812
<b>[sobs]</b>

114
00:08:43,856 --> 00:08:46,317
<b>I still can't be happy.</b>

115
00:08:48,945 --> 00:08:50,363
<b>[Lucas sniffles]</b>

116
00:08:51,155 --> 00:08:54,534
<b>I still can't breathe.</b>
<b>It all feels so heavy.</b>

117
00:08:54,617 --> 00:08:55,868
<b>[Lucas sniffles]</b>

118
00:09:01,332 --> 00:09:05,836
<b>I wanted to tell Edong</b>
<b>that Papa's been caught.</b>

119
00:09:05,920 --> 00:09:07,046
<b>[sniffles]</b>

120
00:09:07,129 --> 00:09:08,923
<b>I wanted to tell him that.</b>

121
00:09:09,840 --> 00:09:12,134
<b>But I can't reach him.</b>

122
00:09:12,843 --> 00:09:15,012
<b>It's like he's completely cut me off.</b>

123
00:09:15,721 --> 00:09:16,806
<b>[sniffles]</b>

124
00:09:18,015 --> 00:09:19,392
<b>[sniffles, exhales heavily]</b>

125
00:09:21,978 --> 00:09:24,021
<b>I almost killed him earlier!</b>

126
00:09:24,105 --> 00:09:26,023
<b>[music becomes tense]</b>

127
00:09:26,107 --> 00:09:30,361
<b>I want nothing more</b>
<b>but beat him senseless!</b>

128
00:09:30,444 --> 00:09:32,989
<b>Beat him until his face</b>
<b>is erased from my mind!</b>

129
00:09:34,156 --> 00:09:35,825
<b>[breathes heavily]</b>

130
00:09:41,455 --> 00:09:43,082
<b>My mother was raped.</b>

131
00:09:44,542 --> 00:09:48,254
<b>[music turns somber]</b>

132
00:09:48,337 --> 00:09:50,381
<b>And I am the consequence.</b>

133
00:09:54,051 --> 00:09:56,554
<b>She hated me the moment I was conceived.</b>

134
00:09:58,806 --> 00:10:00,600
<b>She wanted me gone…</b>

135
00:10:02,685 --> 00:10:05,313
<b>She wanted me gone even before I was born.</b>

136
00:10:07,481 --> 00:10:10,568
<b>She tried to abort me, but she couldn't.</b>

137
00:10:12,570 --> 00:10:16,324
<b>So she was forced to</b>
<b>look at my face every day.</b>

138
00:10:18,034 --> 00:10:20,536
<b>I was the spitting image of her rapist.</b>

139
00:10:20,620 --> 00:10:27,126
<b>[somber music continues]</b>

140
00:10:27,209 --> 00:10:28,502
<b>Are they gone?</b>

141
00:10:29,420 --> 00:10:31,005
<b>The what?</b>

142
00:10:31,088 --> 00:10:33,883
<b>Your destructive</b>
<b>thoughts against your father?</b>

143
00:10:39,597 --> 00:10:43,100
<b>The moment I found out the truth…</b>

144
00:10:43,851 --> 00:10:46,771
<b>I felt so small… so dirty.</b>

145
00:10:49,440 --> 00:10:52,151
<b>I couldn't recognize myself anymore.</b>

146
00:10:57,073 --> 00:10:58,908
<b>My whole balance is…</b>

147
00:10:59,825 --> 00:11:00,785
<b>off.</b>

148
00:11:00,868 --> 00:11:04,580
<b>[somber music continues]</b>

149
00:11:04,664 --> 00:11:07,083
<b>I worked so hard to build that.</b>

150
00:11:10,586 --> 00:11:13,839
<b>And now, I feel like</b>
<b>I'm back to the Erica in high school.</b>

151
00:11:17,343 --> 00:11:19,345
<b>I thought that part of me was dead.</b>

152
00:11:20,846 --> 00:11:22,473
<b>[Erica exhales heavily]</b>

153
00:11:23,140 --> 00:11:25,184
<b>But Marco said,</b>

154
00:11:25,267 --> 00:11:27,311
<b>it doesn't define me.</b>

155
00:11:29,105 --> 00:11:31,357
<b>What happened to my mother</b>

156
00:11:31,440 --> 00:11:33,567
<b>doesn't define my existence.</b>

157
00:11:36,195 --> 00:11:37,696
<b>[Lucas] Erica.</b>

158
00:11:38,989 --> 00:11:40,324
<b>He's right.</b>

159
00:11:42,535 --> 00:11:46,664
<b>But how can you be small and dirty</b>

160
00:11:47,540 --> 00:11:50,709
<b>when you're the only</b>
<b>light in my dark world?</b>

161
00:11:50,793 --> 00:11:55,881
<b>[pensive music playing]</b>

162
00:11:55,965 --> 00:11:57,800
<b>After everything that has happened,</b>

163
00:12:00,511 --> 00:12:03,097
<b>you are still my light.</b>

164
00:12:03,180 --> 00:12:09,645
<b>[pensive music continues]</b>

165
00:12:13,441 --> 00:12:15,401
<b>And that's exactly why</b>
<b>you are not your father, Lucas.</b>

166
00:12:15,484 --> 00:12:17,111
<b>[exhales loudly]</b>

167
00:12:17,194 --> 00:12:19,447
<b>You will never be like him.</b>

168
00:12:21,991 --> 00:12:25,286
<b>[pensive music continues]</b>

169
00:12:25,369 --> 00:12:28,247
<b>[inhales deeply, clears throat]</b>

170
00:12:29,707 --> 00:12:31,333
<b>[sniffles, clears throat]</b>

171
00:12:32,585 --> 00:12:35,546
<b>I've already reached out to NLEA Cavite.</b>

172
00:12:35,629 --> 00:12:38,382
<b>Your father will be</b>
<b>placed under their jurisdiction.</b>

173
00:12:38,466 --> 00:12:40,676
<b>The transfer papers have been settled.</b>

174
00:12:40,759 --> 00:12:42,344
<b>What about my mother's case?</b>

175
00:12:43,262 --> 00:12:47,683
<b>In these cases, they usually prioritize</b>
<b>the newer and more severe.</b>

176
00:12:48,601 --> 00:12:49,602
<b>But once he is convicted,</b>

177
00:12:49,685 --> 00:12:52,104
<b>he will return here to</b>
<b>face the charges of parricide.</b>

178
00:12:53,105 --> 00:12:55,149
<b>I will speak to Locsin.</b>

179
00:12:55,232 --> 00:12:57,568
<b>I will make sure they will file a request</b>

180
00:12:57,651 --> 00:13:00,863
<b>to bring him back to Amurao</b>
<b>after he is sentenced in Cavite.</b>

181
00:13:03,073 --> 00:13:04,700
<b>Thank you.</b>

182
00:13:04,783 --> 00:13:10,831
<b>[pensive music continues, fades]</b>

183
00:13:10,915 --> 00:13:11,832
<b>[Edward] Alice.</b>

184
00:13:12,416 --> 00:13:16,128
<b>Do you think that press conference</b>
<b>changed Edong's mind?</b>

185
00:13:16,212 --> 00:13:17,254
<b>[plate clatters]</b>

186
00:13:17,838 --> 00:13:18,881
<b>Honestly, Uncle?</b>

187
00:13:20,090 --> 00:13:21,842
<b>We're not sure.</b>

188
00:13:24,178 --> 00:13:26,222
<b>But we felt we had to do it.</b>

189
00:13:26,931 --> 00:13:28,974
<b>Regardless if Edong believes us or not,</b>

190
00:13:29,058 --> 00:13:30,643
<b>we have to come clean.</b>

191
00:13:31,727 --> 00:13:33,103
<b>Start over.</b>

192
00:13:33,812 --> 00:13:40,653
<b>[melancholic music playing]</b>

193
00:13:40,736 --> 00:13:41,820
<b>What's wrong?</b>

194
00:13:42,404 --> 00:13:43,781
<b>[sighs sharply]</b>

195
00:13:43,864 --> 00:13:47,117
<b>We said we wanted to start over.</b>

196
00:13:48,285 --> 00:13:50,704
<b>But how am I going to start over</b>

197
00:13:50,788 --> 00:13:53,499
<b>if I can't remember</b>
<b>what happened to me before?</b>

198
00:13:55,042 --> 00:13:57,169
<b>How can I do that?</b>

199
00:13:57,836 --> 00:14:00,422
<b>Everybody's already</b>
<b>faced their demons, and…</b>

200
00:14:00,506 --> 00:14:02,675
<b>I'm the only one who hasn't!</b>

201
00:14:07,096 --> 00:14:08,347
<b>[sighs]</b>

202
00:14:12,393 --> 00:14:13,769
<b>[Alice exhales heavily]</b>

203
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:25,364
<b>What if you can only start over…</b>

204
00:14:26,365 --> 00:14:28,367
<b>when you learn to trust yourself?</b>

205
00:14:30,619 --> 00:14:33,789
<b>If your mind and body is telling you</b>

206
00:14:35,082 --> 00:14:36,542
<b>"Enough".</b>

207
00:14:37,793 --> 00:14:42,506
<b>You don't need to pressure</b>
<b>yourself to know everything.</b>

208
00:14:44,258 --> 00:14:46,468
<b>Then, maybe that's what</b>
<b>you're supposed to do, Alice.</b>

209
00:14:47,970 --> 00:14:49,638
<b>Isn't that</b>

210
00:14:49,722 --> 00:14:51,765
<b>what your therapist is also telling you?</b>

211
00:14:55,102 --> 00:14:56,103
<b>So…</b>

212
00:14:57,688 --> 00:14:59,690
<b>[sniffles] I'll just</b>
<b>have to forget everything then?</b>

213
00:15:00,316 --> 00:15:03,402
<b>I'll just let all my</b>
<b>memories get buried,</b>

214
00:15:03,485 --> 00:15:04,737
<b>forever?</b>

215
00:15:06,113 --> 00:15:08,073
<b>I started sleepwalking</b>

216
00:15:08,157 --> 00:15:11,660
<b>because of all those</b>
<b>memories and all that trauma.</b>

217
00:15:11,744 --> 00:15:13,120
<b>But,</b>

218
00:15:13,203 --> 00:15:16,248
<b>Alice, you said it's been a while</b>
<b>since it happened again, right?</b>

219
00:15:16,957 --> 00:15:20,753
<b>That you handle yourself better now.</b>

220
00:15:20,836 --> 00:15:22,254
<b>Yes. But--</b>

221
00:15:22,338 --> 00:15:24,715
<b>But Alice…</b>

222
00:15:24,798 --> 00:15:26,133
<b>[unsettling music playing]</b>

223
00:15:26,216 --> 00:15:27,301
<b>think about it.</b>

224
00:15:28,719 --> 00:15:30,262
<b>Okay?</b>

225
00:15:30,346 --> 00:15:31,513
<b>I don't want your efforts</b>

226
00:15:32,431 --> 00:15:33,474
<b>to go to waste.</b>

227
00:15:34,516 --> 00:15:36,143
<b>You've already made great progress.</b>

228
00:15:36,936 --> 00:15:38,062
<b>Okay?</b>

229
00:15:38,562 --> 00:15:41,023
<b>There's nothing you should forget.</b>

230
00:15:41,106 --> 00:15:43,108
<b>There's nothing you should give up on.</b>

231
00:15:44,193 --> 00:15:46,946
<b>Maybe knowing something's wrong is enough.</b>

232
00:15:47,029 --> 00:15:49,198
<b>And all that's left for you to do</b>

233
00:15:49,782 --> 00:15:51,450
<b>is to let go.</b>

234
00:15:53,035 --> 00:15:54,244
<b>For you to finally…</b>

235
00:15:55,079 --> 00:15:56,080
<b>be at peace.</b>

236
00:15:56,622 --> 00:15:58,707
<b>That's what's important, right?</b>

237
00:15:58,791 --> 00:16:05,506
<b>[unsettling music continues]</b>

238
00:16:05,589 --> 00:16:06,840
<b>I--</b>

239
00:16:08,467 --> 00:16:09,843
<b>Alright, Uncle.</b>

240
00:16:11,345 --> 00:16:12,429
<b>I'll think about it.</b>

241
00:16:17,309 --> 00:16:24,024
<b>[unsettling music intensifies]</b>

242
00:16:31,490 --> 00:16:33,033
<b>[music fades]</b>

243
00:16:40,207 --> 00:16:41,792
<b>[door closes, lock clicks]</b>

244
00:16:45,921 --> 00:16:46,964
<b>Ma'am?</b>

245
00:16:47,715 --> 00:16:51,343
<b>Ma'am Alice and Ma'am Mel aren't home yet.</b>
<b>But you have a visitor.</b>

246
00:16:52,136 --> 00:16:53,721
<b>-Visitor?</b>
<b>-Yes.</b>

247
00:16:58,475 --> 00:16:59,518
<b>Erica.</b>

248
00:17:08,402 --> 00:17:10,070
<b>I'm sorry. Uh…</b>

249
00:17:11,030 --> 00:17:13,365
<b>I came here because,</b>

250
00:17:13,449 --> 00:17:15,659
<b>there's something I wanted to give you.</b>

251
00:17:16,535 --> 00:17:18,245
<b>[breathes deeply]</b>

252
00:17:18,328 --> 00:17:20,164
<b>[papers rustle]</b>

253
00:17:21,206 --> 00:17:24,960
<b>[sniffles]</b>

254
00:17:25,044 --> 00:17:28,922
<b>These are birthday cards</b>
<b>I made for you. [sniffles]</b>

255
00:17:29,965 --> 00:17:33,469
<b>Every year for 14 years…</b>

256
00:17:35,054 --> 00:17:39,391
<b>I never stopped.</b>
<b>Even though you weren't here.</b>

257
00:17:39,475 --> 00:17:42,186
<b>Even though I couldn't send them to you.</b>

258
00:17:43,937 --> 00:17:45,606
<b>I know it's not even your birthday.</b>

259
00:17:47,399 --> 00:17:48,817
<b>But…</b>

260
00:17:48,901 --> 00:17:53,989
<b>I just felt I had to</b>
<b>bring this and give it to you.</b>

261
00:17:55,240 --> 00:17:57,034
<b>I can't explain why.</b>

262
00:18:01,246 --> 00:18:04,625
<b>I kept them all because in my mind…</b>

263
00:18:06,085 --> 00:18:07,669
<b>you might come back.</b>

264
00:18:08,420 --> 00:18:10,672
<b>Maybe… [sobs]</b>

265
00:18:10,756 --> 00:18:12,508
<b>…I'd have my sister back.</b>

266
00:18:17,763 --> 00:18:19,014
<b>I know…</b>

267
00:18:20,349 --> 00:18:23,393
<b>it's hard to forget everything Mom said.</b>

268
00:18:24,061 --> 00:18:25,979
<b>I know it hurts.</b>

269
00:18:26,063 --> 00:18:28,107
<b>And I'm not defending her.</b>

270
00:18:28,190 --> 00:18:29,566
<b>Mama is wrong.</b>

271
00:18:30,400 --> 00:18:35,531
<b>[somber music playing]</b>

272
00:18:37,032 --> 00:18:38,575
<b>But Erica…</b>

273
00:18:39,326 --> 00:18:40,953
<b>I celebrate you.</b>

274
00:18:43,455 --> 00:18:45,749
<b>I celebrate because you're in the world.</b>

275
00:18:47,417 --> 00:18:49,878
<b>I'm thankful to you, Erica.</b>

276
00:18:50,921 --> 00:18:53,882
<b>Even though I'm no</b>
<b>longer a part of your life.</b>

277
00:18:54,466 --> 00:18:56,677
<b>[Althea sobbing]</b>

278
00:18:56,760 --> 00:18:58,679
<b>Because you are…</b>

279
00:19:01,932 --> 00:19:07,020
<b>a big part and will</b>
<b>always be part of my life.</b>

280
00:19:07,563 --> 00:19:14,111
<b>[somber music continues]</b>

281
00:19:19,116 --> 00:19:21,493
<b>I miss you so much, Erica.</b>

282
00:19:24,413 --> 00:19:26,915
<b>Not just the way we used to be…</b>

283
00:19:28,625 --> 00:19:30,460
<b>I also miss…</b>

284
00:19:31,378 --> 00:19:33,380
<b>what we could have been today.</b>

285
00:19:34,173 --> 00:19:37,009
<b>If none of it had ever happened.</b>

286
00:19:41,972 --> 00:19:44,141
<b>I love you, Erica.</b>

287
00:19:44,975 --> 00:19:51,607
<b>[somber music continues]</b>

288
00:20:11,293 --> 00:20:13,212
<i><b>Happy Birthday, Erica!</b></i>

289
00:20:16,715 --> 00:20:19,718
<b>[young Erica] </b><i><b>Thank you, Thea.</b></i>
<i><b>You're so sweet.</b></i>

290
00:20:25,515 --> 00:20:26,767
<b>[sobs]</b>

291
00:20:26,850 --> 00:20:35,234
<b>[somber music continues]</b>

292
00:20:36,985 --> 00:20:38,278
<b>[sobs]</b>

293
00:20:52,542 --> 00:20:56,797
<b>[sobbing continues]</b>

294
00:21:03,845 --> 00:21:06,723
<b>-Althea's on her way here.</b>
<b>-[music fades]</b>

295
00:21:06,807 --> 00:21:08,684
<b>Her father's bringing here.</b>

296
00:21:08,767 --> 00:21:11,979
<b>The church asked me</b>
<b>for a favor. I couldn't say no.</b>

297
00:21:12,062 --> 00:21:15,065
<b>But I'll be quick.</b>
<b>It'll just take a few hours.</b>

298
00:21:15,148 --> 00:21:17,901
<b>You can go ahead, Uncle.</b>
<b>I’ll be the one to wait for Althea.</b>

299
00:21:17,985 --> 00:21:19,486
<b>-Are you sure?</b>
<b>-Yes.</b>

300
00:21:19,569 --> 00:21:21,321
<b>Don't worry.</b>

301
00:21:21,405 --> 00:21:22,864
<b>Thanks, Alice.</b>

302
00:21:23,740 --> 00:21:25,617
<b>I'll go now.</b>

303
00:21:25,701 --> 00:21:26,994
<b>Uncle?</b>

304
00:21:31,081 --> 00:21:33,667
<b>I was… I was wondering…</b>

305
00:21:35,460 --> 00:21:38,046
<b>do you know of a house that…</b>

306
00:21:39,339 --> 00:21:41,300
<b>looks a bit old.</b>

307
00:21:41,383 --> 00:21:44,052
<b>Um, it's a bit dirty inside.</b>

308
00:21:44,136 --> 00:21:45,304
<b>There are many stuff.</b>

309
00:21:45,846 --> 00:21:47,723
<b>There's a lot of</b>
<b>antiques or something like that.</b>

310
00:21:47,806 --> 00:21:52,978
<b>[unsettling music playing]</b>

311
00:21:53,061 --> 00:21:56,732
<b>[young Alice crying] </b><i><b>Mama! Papa!</b></i>

312
00:22:01,528 --> 00:22:04,573
<b>Why, Uncle? Is that place familiar to you?</b>

313
00:22:06,074 --> 00:22:07,659
<b>[chuckles] No, no, no.</b>

314
00:22:07,743 --> 00:22:10,746
<b>I just remembered something that I need</b>
<b>to take to where I’m going.</b>

315
00:22:11,371 --> 00:22:14,666
<b>Never mind,</b>
<b>I’ll just stop by the store instead.</b>

316
00:22:14,750 --> 00:22:17,794
<b>[unsettling music continues]</b>

317
00:22:17,878 --> 00:22:18,837
<b>[phone chimes]</b>

318
00:22:23,133 --> 00:22:24,301
<b>What is it?</b>

319
00:22:24,384 --> 00:22:28,680
<b>Lucas and Edong’s father has been jailed.</b>

320
00:22:29,806 --> 00:22:33,435
<b>Remember?</b>
<b>He killed their mother years ago.</b>

321
00:22:33,518 --> 00:22:34,728
<b>[exhales sharply]</b>

322
00:22:34,811 --> 00:22:36,271
<b>That was a long time ago.</b>

323
00:22:37,647 --> 00:22:39,232
<b>But I'm glad to hear that.</b>

324
00:22:39,858 --> 00:22:42,694
<b>Men who hurt women and children</b>

325
00:22:43,737 --> 00:22:45,530
<b>are a plague on society.</b>

326
00:22:46,239 --> 00:22:48,700
<b>They should be held</b>
<b>accountable for their actions.</b>

327
00:22:48,784 --> 00:22:54,247
<b>[unsettling music continues]</b>

328
00:22:54,331 --> 00:22:56,541
<b>Alright, I'll get going.</b>

329
00:22:57,501 --> 00:22:58,543
<b>Okay.</b>

330
00:23:03,381 --> 00:23:05,884
<b>[music turns dramatic]</b>

331
00:23:05,967 --> 00:23:08,011
<b>Auntie! Auntie.</b>

332
00:23:08,595 --> 00:23:11,431
<b>-You should've called me.</b>
<b>-Over there.</b>

333
00:23:13,308 --> 00:23:14,559
<b>[Christina] Over there.</b>

334
00:23:14,643 --> 00:23:21,733
<b>[dramatic music intensifies]</b>

335
00:23:30,826 --> 00:23:32,536
<i><b>There's something</b></i>
<i><b>I need to confess to you.</b></i>

336
00:23:32,619 --> 00:23:35,330
<i><b>I almost left</b></i>
<i><b>you when Chloe was still a baby.</b></i>

337
00:23:35,413 --> 00:23:37,999
<i><b>I still think about</b></i>
<i><b>the dreams I didn't achieve.</b></i>

338
00:23:38,708 --> 00:23:40,794
<b>[dispatch] </b><i><b>Unit 12, Unit 12,</b></i>
<i><b>requesting immediate backup.</b></i>

339
00:23:40,877 --> 00:23:43,171
<i><b>There's a shooting in</b></i>
<i><b>San Felipe. Officers down.</b></i>

340
00:23:43,255 --> 00:23:45,549
<b>[officer] </b><i><b>Maybe we should leave.</b></i>
<i><b>They need us in San Felipe.</b></i>

341
00:23:45,632 --> 00:23:46,925
<i><b>We're on our way to the location.</b></i>

342
00:23:48,301 --> 00:23:49,970
<i><b>Erica, something happened.</b></i>

343
00:23:50,053 --> 00:23:51,721
<b>[Annette] </b><i><b>We need to find her.</b></i>

344
00:23:51,805 --> 00:23:54,474
<i><b>I'm begging you, please find my daughter!</b></i>

345
00:23:57,102 --> 00:23:59,104
<i><b>Help! Help!</b></i>
